<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1907-12-10T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1907-12-10T00:00:00-05:00" n="392" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d392">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 3123/8.</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Minister <persName type="from">Graves</persName> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Stockholm</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1907-12-10"><hi rend="italic">December 10,
                                    1907</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>(States that the funeral of the King of Sweden will take place on the
                            19th of December, and that Great Britain, Germany, Austria, and other
                            countries will be represented by a member of the royal family. France
                            will probably have special representatives.)</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>